@node Main "JackTrap - Documentation"

                              'JackTrap' 1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'JackTrap' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} where you have to get the jack
out of the 'trap'. At the start of a game, the jack is located at
the fourth position under a series of 10 cards which are all face
down. An empty square as well as a pack containing the 41
remaining cards, all face down, are located at the bottom of the
game board.

  The jack will move according to the colour shown on the card
located above it, if the colour is red (heart or diamond), the
jack will move one position to the left. While a black colour
(spade or club) will move the jack toward the right. When the
jack gets from the left (or right) of the game board to the empty
square before the pack is empty, the game is won...

  Have fun!

