@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "JackTrap" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that JackTrap runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a card that is located above the jack,
that card will be turned over and then be removed from the game
board. If the colour shown on that card is red (heart or diamond),
the jack will move one position to the left. While a black colour
(spade or club) will move the jack toward the right. The removed
card will be replaced by a card from the pack at the bottom of the
game board, if there are any that remains, of course...

  Continue the game until the jack gets from one end of the game
board (either the right or left end) to the empty square or there
are no remaining cards in the pack...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

